akitaDAO.descr: the app ID of the Akita DAO

akitaDAOEscrow.descr: the escrow account to use when making payments to the Akita DAO

bidAsset.descr: the asset that is being used for bidding in the auction

bidFee.descr: the percentage fee to take for the raffle on each bid in hundreds to support two decimals

bidID.descr: the id or index of the last bid

bidMinimumIncrease.descr: the smallest amount each new bid need increment the auction price

bidTotal.descr: the total sum of all bids

creatorRoyalty.descr: the royalty percentage the creator will get for the auction

endTimestamp.descr: the round that the auction ends on

findWinnerCursors.descr:
cursors to track iteration of finding winner
index being for the bid iteration
amountIndex being the index for the amount of the bids seen

gateID.descr: the gate ID to use to check if the user is qualified to bid in the auction

highestBid.descr: highest bid the contract has received thus far

isPrizeBox.descr: whether or not the prize is an asset or a prize box

marketplace.descr:
The address of the marketplace that created the auction to send the fee to

IMPORTANT: this is a double sided marketplace fee contract
the marketplace referred to internally in the contract
is the listing side marketplace.
the buyer side marketplace provides their address at
the time of purchase

marketplaceRoyalties.descr: the royalty percentage each side of the market will take for the auction

prizeClaimed.descr: whether the prize has been claimed

raffleAmount.descr: the total amount collected for the loser raffle

rafflePrizeClaimed.descr: whether the raffle winner has claimed their prize

raffleWinner.descr: the winning address of the raffle

refundCount.descr: the number of bids that have been refunded

refundMBRCursor.descr: cursor to track iteration of MBR refunds

startTimestamp.descr: the unix time that the auction starts on

startingBid.descr: the starting amount to begin bids at

uniqueAddressCount.descr:
we count how many unique addresses bid so we can
properly get each bids % of the total bid amount

version.descr: the current version of the contract

vrfFailureCount.descr: counter for how many times we've failed to get rng from the beacon

weightTotals.descr: totals for each box of weights for our skip list

weightedBidTotal.descr: the total sum of all highest bids

weightsBoxCount.descr: the number of boxes allocated to tracking weights

winningTicket.descr:
we get the winning number from the randomness beacon
after the auction ends & we have ran findWinner
to compile our list

methods.name: cancel
methods.desc:
deletes the application & returns the mbr + asset
to the seller IF the auction hasn't started

returns.desc: a boolean of whether the auction is live
a boolean of whether the address has bid in the auction

methods.name: optin

args.name: asset
args.desc: The asset to be opted into

methods.desc: optin tells the contract to opt into an asa
